arrs Mill Dam to Line Creek. Most of Starrs Mill Park will be under 5 to 7 feet of water. The flood waters will surround the mill and begin to enter the building. The water level will reach the foundation of a building next to the mill and be one half foot below the USGS gage house. A loss of data transmission will be possible."},{"stage":16,"statement":"Significant flooding expands further into the woodlands and fields along the creek downstream from the Starrs Mill Dam to Line Creek. Most of Starrs Mill Park will be under 4 to 6 feet of water. The flood waters will be hitting the bottom of the mill. The water level will be around one foot deep over the wooden platform where the USGS gage house is located."},{"stage":15,"statement":"Moderate flooding begins. Significant flooding occurs in the woodlands and fields along the creek downstream from the Starrs Mill Dam to Line Creek. Most of Starrs Mill Park will be under 3 to 5 feet of water. The flood waters will approach the bottom of the mill and be flowing through the concrete spillway around one foot deep. The water level will reach the top of the wooden platform where the USGS gage house is located."},{"stage":14,"statement":"Minor flooding expands further into the woodlands and fields along the creek downstream from the Starrs Mill Dam to Line Creek. Most of Starrs Mill Park will be under 2 to 4 feet of water. The flood waters will surround the steps leading to the mill and cover the concrete spillway around one half foot deep."},{"stage":13,"statement":"Minor flooding continues to expand into the woodlands and fields along the creek downstream from the Starrs Mill Dam to Line Creek. Most of Starrs Mill Park including the rock access road will be under 1 to 3 feet of water. The flood waters will surround the steps leading to the mill and cover the concrete spillway."},{"stage":11,"statement":"Minor flooding continues in the woodlands and fields along the creek downstream from the Starrs Mill Dam to Line Creek. The parking lot will be under a foot of water at Starrs Mill Park. The rock access road leading to the park will begin to flood. Flood waters will be flowing through the concrete spillway. "},{"stage":10,"statement":"Flood stage is reached. Minor flooding begins in the woodlands and fields along the creek downstream from the Starrs Mill Dam to Line Creek. The parking lot will begin to flood at Starrs Mill Park. Concrete picnic tables at the park will be under water. Flood waters will begin to flow through the concrete spillway."},{"stage":8,"statement":"Bankfull conditions are reached along the creek downstream from the Starrs Mill Dam to Line Creek. Some concrete picnic tables will be surrounded by water. Low lying areas of woodlands and fields will begin to flood further downstream."}]},"images":{"probability":{"weekint":{"stage":"","flow":"","volume":""},"entperiod":{"stage":"","flow":"","volume":""},"shortrange":""},"hydrograph":{"default":"https://water.noaa.gov/resources/hydrographs/smfg1_hg.png","floodcat":"https://water.noaa.gov/resources/hydrographs/smfg1_record.png"},"photos":[]},"dataAttribution":[{"abbrev":"US Geological Survey","text":"USGS--Water Resources of the United States","title":"US Geological Survey","url":"https://waterdata.usgs.gov/nwis"},{"abbrev":"USGS","text":"02344748","title":"Observations courtesy of U.S. Geological Survey","url":"https://waterdata.usgs.gov/nwis/inventory/?site_no=02344748"}],"impactsLowWaters":[],"normalThreshold":{"value":0,"units":"ft"},"hydronotes":[{"statement":"Automatic observations from this river gauge will soon be discontinued if funding is not identified.  Contact webmaster at link below if you can help.","effective":"0101","expiration":"1231"},{"statement":"River forecasts will be discontinued if funding for river gauge is not identified.  Contact webmaster at link below if you can help.","effective":"0101","expiration":"1231"}],"datums":{"vertical":{"value":[]},"horizontal":{"value":[]},"notes":{"value":[]}}